text: @EricGiddens4IA will be sworn into office sometime next week after the official canvas of the results from the special election. “I’m just excited to get to work,” he told @RadioIowa #ialegis #iapolitics
author: okayhenderson

text: “There was just so much enthusiasm & support for this campaign in such a short amount of time that I’ve been overwhelmed...this is a really, really important & special thing & I’m just incredibly grateful,” @EricGiddens4IA told @RadioIowa. #ialegis #iapolitics
author: okayhenderson

text: “I’m proud of my team. I’m proud of Black Hawk County Republicans. We worked hard the past 3 weeks & we laid it all on the field,” @waltrogersforIA told @RadioIowa. #iapolitics
author: okayhenderson

text: “I think this district is moving to the left...added on top of that were all these presidential candidates that came in & energized their base & energized their volunteers, so it was a perfect storm,” @waltrogersforIA told @RadioIowa in conceding state senate race. #iapolitics
author: okayhenderson
